translations: n.（尤指在某领域或职业中）著名，卓越；名人，权威人士；阁下，大人（对天主教红衣主教的尊称）；高地，山丘；隆凸，隆起

sentences.sentence: Many of the pilots were to achieve eminence in the aeronautical world.
sentences.translation: 其中的很多飞行员后来在航空界都取得了显赫的声名。

sentences.sentence: We presented a report of the thenar eminence.
sentences.translation: 我们呈上一份关于鱼际隆起的报告。

sentences.sentence: So Americans are wrong to think their "pre-eminence is America's to lose".
sentences.translation: 所以美国人认为他们的“出类拔萃就是是美国的失去”这个想法是错误的。
